properties.areaDesc: Santa Ana Mountains and Foothills; San Bernardino and Riverside County Valleys-The Inland Empire
properties.headline: Wind Advisory issued March 2 at 1:42AM PST until March 3 at 12:00PM PST by NWS San Diego CA
properties.description:
* WHAT...North winds 15 to 25 mph with gusts to 40 mph.

* WHERE...The northern Inland Empire, mainly in a corridor between
Cajon Pass and Corona. Also, the ridges and coastal slopes of
the Santa Ana Mountains.

* WHEN...Until noon PST Tuesday.

* IMPACTS...Gusty winds could blow around unsecured objects.
Tree limbs could be blown down and a few power outages may
result.
properties.instruction:
Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high
profile vehicle. Secure outdoor objects.

NWSheadline: WIND ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL NOON PST TUESDAY
